file.name: openapi.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
servers:
  - url: 'http://www.networknt.com/v1'
info:
  version: 1.0.13
  title: PDF test
  description: PDF test
  contact:
    name: Gavin chen
    email: gavin.chenyan@gmail.com
  license:
    name: Apache 2.0
    url: 'http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html'
paths:
  /pdf/report:
    get:
      description: get a updated plan PDF file after plan update operation. (MOCK)
      operationId: getPlanReport
      responses:
        '200':
          description: PDF file as byte array.
          content:
            application/octet-stream:
              schema:
                type: string
                format: byte
        400:
          description: Bad Request.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        401:
          description: Not Authenticated.  The request requires the user or application to be authenticated.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        403:
          description: Forbidden.  The user or application is not authorized to perform this operation.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        404:
          description: Resource not found
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        500:
          description: Internal Server Error.  An unexpected error has occured.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        default:
          description: unexpected error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
    post:
      description: upload  a pdf or images file. (MOCK)
      operationId: postPlanReport
      requestBody:
        content:
          multipart/form-data:
            schema:
             type: object
             properties:      # Request parts
              name:            # Part 1 (string value)
               type: string
              profileFile:  # Part 2 (an image)
               type: string
               format: binary
      responses:
        '200':
          description: PDF file as byte array.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        400:
          description: Bad Request.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        401:
          description: Not Authenticated.  The request requires the user or application to be authenticated.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        403:
          description: Forbidden.  The user or application is not authorized to perform this operation.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        404:
          description: Resource not found
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        500:
          description: Internal Server Error.  An unexpected error has occured.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        default:
          description: unexpected error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
components:
  schemas:
    Error:
      type: object
      required:
        - statusCode
        - code
        - message
        - description
      properties:
        statusCode:
          type: integer
          format: int32
        code:
          type: string
        message:
          type: string
        description:
          type: string
